4. Problems Adapt to the Student

A textbook gives the same problem to everyone.

But a thinking canvas can adapt difficulty dynamically.

Example:

If a student struggles with:

x² − 5x + 6 = 0

The system might:
	•	break it into factoring hints
	•	show geometric visualization
	•	compare with previous solved examples
	•	highlight pattern recognition

Learning becomes personalized feedback loops.

